    Unit Upgrades

    War Suns

    • University War Sun

      Hylar War Sun

      Other players' units in this system lose Planetary Shield.

      • Sustain Damage
      • Bombardment 4 (x3)

      | Cost 10 | Combat 4 | Move 3 | Capacity 6 |

    • Prototype War Sun

      Gashlai War Sun

      Other players' units in this system lose Planetary Shield.

      This unit and other units moving at the same time can move into and through supernovas.

      • Sustain Damage
      • Bombardment 3 (x3)

      | Cost 12 | Combat 3 | Move 2 | Capacity 6 |

    • The Dragon, Freed

      The Obsidian War Sun

      While you own this card, you can only have 1 war sun.

      When this unit uses Bombardment, it uses it against each planet in its system and each adjacent system, even yours, ignoring Planetary Shield.

      • Sustain Damage
      • Bombardment 3 (x3)

      | Cost 12 | Combat 3 | Move 2 | Capacity 6 |

    Flagships

    • Echo of Ascension

      Precursor Flagship

      Keep this card in your play area and adjust the printed values of your flagship by the indicated amounts.

      | Combat 1 + | Move +1 | Capacity +2 |

    Dreadnoughts

    • Super-Dreadnought

      L1Z1X Dreadnought

      This unit cannot be destroyed by "Spark" action cards.

      • Sustain Damage
      • Bombardment 4

      | Cost 4 | Combat 5 | Move 2 | Capacity 2 |

    • Dawncrusher

      Letnev Dreadnought

      This unit cannot be destroyed by "Spark" action cards.

      • Sustain Damage
      • Bombardment 4

      | Cost 3 | Combat 5 | Move 2 | Capacity 1 |

    • Exotrireme

      N'orr Dreadnought

      This unit cannot be destroyed by "Spark" action cards.

      After a round of space combat, you may destroy this unit to destroy up to 2 ships in this system.

      • Sustain Damage
      • Bombardment 4 (x2)

      | Cost 4 | Combat 4 | Move 2 | Capacity 1 |

    Carriers

    • Vortexer

      Vuil'Raith Carrier

      Capture other players' infantry and fighters that are destroyed or removed in this unit's system or an adjacent system. At the start of your turn, you may spend captured infantry or fighters to place equivalent units from your reinforcements in this system.

      | Cost 3 | Combat 9 | Move 2 | Capacity 6 |

    • Ambassador

      Deepwrought Carrier

      After you commit units, if units transported by Ambassadors are the only units committed to a planet, you may place those units into coexistence instead.

      | Cost 3 | Combat 9 | Move 2 | Capacity 6 |

    • Advanced Carrier

      Sol Carrier

      • Sustain Damage

      | Cost 3 | Combat 9 | Move 2 | Capacity 8 |

    Crusiers

    • Ahk Syl Fier

      Creuss Cruiser

      At the start of your turn, you may place or move a Creuss wormhole token into this system.

      | Cost 2 | Combat 6 | Move 3 | Capacity 1 |

    • Saggitaria

      Keleres Cruiser

      • Sustain Damage

      | Cost 2 | Combat 6 | Move 3 | Capacity 1 |

    • Corsair

      Mentak Cruiser

      If the active system contains another player's non-fighter ships, this unit can move through systems that contain other players' ships.

      | Cost 2 | Combat 6 | Move 3 | Capacity 2 |

    Destroyers

    • Strike Wing Alpha

      Argent Destroyer

      When this unit uses Anti-Fighter Barrage, each result of 9 or 10 also destroys 1 of your opponent's infantry in the space area of the active system.

      • Anti-Fighter Barrage 6 (x3)

      | Cost 1 | Combat 7 | Move 2 | Capacity 1 |

    • Linkship

      Ral Nel Destroyer

      When this unit retreats, you may destroy 1 ship in the active system that is damaged or does not have Sustain Damage.

      • Anti-Fighter Barrage 6 (x3)

      | Cost 1 | Combat 8 | Move 2 |

    • Exile

      Rebellion Destroyer

      This unit can move through systems that contain other players' ships.

      • Anti-Fighter Barrage 6 (x3)

      | Cost 1 | Combat 8 | Move 4 |

    Fighters

    • Triune

      Empyrean Fighter

      This unit may move without being transported.

      Fighters in excess of your ships' capacity count against your fleet pool.

      You may remove 3 of your fighters from systems that contain or are adjacent to a player's units to cancel an action card played by that player.

      | Cost 1 | Combat 7 | Move 2 |

    • Hybrid Crystal Fighter

      Naalu Fighter

      This unit may move without being transported.

      Each fighter in excess of your ships' capacity counts as of a ship against your fleet pool.

      | Cost 1 | Combat 7 | Move 2 |

    • Morphwing

      Naaz-Rokha Fighter

      This unit may move without being transported.

      Fighters in excess of your ships' capacity count against your fleet pool.

      This unit can be committed during an invasion; either return it to the space area or replace it with one infantry at the end of combat.

      | Cost 1 | Combat 7 | Move 2 |

    Mechs

    • Eidolon Terminus

      Vuil'Raith Mech

      Keep this card in your play area; the Combat value of your mechs is reduced by 1.

      | Combat 1 |

    • Eidolon Landwaster

      Naaz-Rokha Mech

      Keep this card in your play area; your mechs roll 1 additional die during combat.

      | Combat + |

    • Valefar Prime

      Nekro Mech

      Keep this card in your play area; the Cost value of your mechs is reduced by 1.

      | Cost 1 |

    Infantry

    • Letani Warrior

      Arborec Infantry

      • Production 2

      | Cost 1 | Combat 7 |

    • Yin Clone

      Yin Infantry

      After this unit is destroyed or removed, place the unit on this card.

      At the start of the status phase, place each unit that is on this card on a planet you control.

      | Cost 1 | Combat 7 |

    • Guild Agents

      Yssaril Infantry

      After you move this unit into a system that contains another player's units, you may look at that player's action cards and take 1 of them.

      | Cost 1 | Combat 7 |

    Space Docks

    • Helios Entity

      Bastion Space Dock

      This unit's Production value is equal to 2 more than the resource value of this planet.

      The resource value of this planet is increased by 2.

      Up to 3 fighters in this system do not count against your ships' capacity.

      • Production X+2

    • Production Biomes

      Hacan Space Dock

      Up to 3 fighters in this system do not count against your ships' capacity.

      When this unit uses Production, you may spend 1 token from your strategy pool to gain 4 trade goods and choose another player to gain 2 trade goods.

      • Production 9

    • Floating Factories

      Saar Space Dock

      This unit is placed in a space area instead of on a planet.

      This unit can move and retreat as if it were a ship. If this unit is blockaded, it is destroyed.

      • Production 7

      | Move 2 | Capacity 5 |

    PDS

    • Hel-Titan

      Titan PDS

      This unit is treated as both a structure and a ground force. It cannot be transported.

      You may use this unit's Space Cannon ability against ships that are adjacent to this unit's system.

      • Planetary Shield
      • Space Cannon 5
      • Sustain Damage
      • Production 1

      | Combat 5 |

    • Justicier Rail

      Winnu PDS

      You may use this unit's Space Cannon ability against ships that are adjacent to this unit's system.

      Hits produced by this unit must be assigned to non-fighter ships if able.

      • Planetary Shield
      • Space Cannon 5

    • Keeper Matrix

      Xxcha PDS

      You may use this unit's Space Cannon ability against ships that are adjacent to this unit's system.

      • Planetary Shield
      • Space Cannon 5 (x2)
